   <children>
      <AnchorPane>
         <children>
            <Rectangle arcHeight="5.0" arcWidth="5.0" height="65.0" stroke="TRANSPARENT" strokeType="INSIDE" width="262.0">
               <fill>
                  <LinearGradient endX="1.0" endY="1.0">
                     <stops>
                        <Stop>
                           <color>
                              <Color red="0.23333333432674408" green="0.9744444489479065" blue="1.0" />
                           </color>
                        </Stop>
                        <Stop offset="1.0">
                           <color>
                              <Color red="1.0" green="1.0" blue="1.0" />
                           </color>
                        </Stop>
                     </stops>
                  </LinearGradient>
               </fill>
            </Rectangle>
            <Button layoutX="16.0" layoutY="16.0" mnemonicParsing="false" onAction="#switchToMainScene" text="Back" />
         </children>
      </AnchorPane>
      <ScrollPane fitToWidth="true" layoutX="3.0" layoutY="62.0" VBox.vgrow="ALWAYS">
         <content>
            <VBox>
               <children>
                  <Label prefHeight="32.0" text="Hash Table">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="System Bold" size="22.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label prefHeight="32.0" text="Student Record System">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="System Bold" size="14.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label text="A static array can be comparable to a parking lot since during its construction it is only limited to a fixed amount of parking spaces." wrapText="true">
                     <font>
                        <Font size="11.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <AnchorPane prefHeight="203.0" prefWidth="179.0">
                     <children>
                        <ImageView fitHeight="155.0" fitWidth="240.0" layoutX="-1.0" layoutY="31.0" pickOnBounds="true" preserveRatio="true">
                           <image>
                              <Image url="@8-student-card.jpg" />
                           </image>
                        </ImageView>
                     </children></AnchorPane>
                  <Label prefHeight="32.0" prefWidth="157.0" text="Access">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="System Bold" size="14.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label text="To access a specific record of a student such as grades or contact information, a student ID must be first given to the ststem. The system then clauclates the location (bucket) where the information you want to access is stored using the provided ID which is similar to hash tables wherein a key is provided and hashed to determine the location of a specific value." wrapText="true">
                     <font>
                        <Font size="11.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label prefHeight="32.0" prefWidth="157.0" text="Search">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="System Bold" size="14.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label text="It is also possible to serach based on other criterias other than ID such as names or grades which is similar to how a has table can search for values based on keys." wrapText="true">
                     <font>
                        <Font size="11.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label prefHeight="32.0" prefWidth="157.0" text="Insert">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="System Bold" size="14.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label text="In adding a new student, information such as name, student ID, and contact details is collected and stored in the system. The ID serves as a unique identifier that is used to determine which location (bucket) that information would go into. Similarly, in a hash table, the insertion of data involves both hashing and adding the data in that specific location." wrapText="true">
                     <font>
                        <Font size="11.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label prefHeight="32.0" prefWidth="157.0" text="Delete">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="System Bold" size="14.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Label text="When removing student records from the system, a search operation is conducted using their ID, the data is then located and deleted from the system to give space for other records. This is similar to hash tables in which you search, locate, and remove a key-value pair." wrapText="true">
                     <font>
                        <Font size="11.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
               </children>
            </VBox>
         </content>
      </ScrollPane>
   </children>
